Snake Game

This is a simple implementation of the classic Snake game in C++ using the ncurses library for terminal-based graphics.

Gameplay

Use the arrow keys to control the snake's movement: Up, Down, Left, and Right.
The objective of the game is to eat the food (*) to increase your score.
Avoid hitting the walls or the snake's own body, as this will end the game.
The game ends when you press the 'q' key or collide with a wall or the snake's body.

Controls

Arrow Up: Move the snake upwards.
Arrow Down: Move the snake downwards.
Arrow Left: Move the snake to the left.
Arrow Right: Move the snake to the right.
'q': Quit the game.

Game Elements
Snake: The player-controlled character represented by the 'o' symbol.
Food: The target for the snake to eat, represented by the '@' symbol.
Score: The score represents the number of times the snake has eaten the food.

Enjoy the Game!
Have fun playing the Snake game! Try to achieve the highest score without hitting any walls or the snake's body. Good luck!
